<title type="html"><![CDATA[[JOKE] Bloated Aero! (Because regular Aero isn't big enough)]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=5249&amp;p=22901#p22901"><![CDATA[
This all started as a flaw in Sagorpirbd's <a href="http://sagorpirbd.deviantart.com/art/Aero-7-Themes-for-Windows-10-523979941" class="postlink">Windows 7 Aero for Windows 10</a> Visual Style. The caption buttons didn't look quite right to me, but I thought they were hilarious for some reason, and so I ported them to BorderSkin. Then, I decided to create a Start Menu skin and Button to match. Not sure whether that was anything more than an excuse to share the BorderSkin theme here, but nonetheless there's a Start Menu skin too. Behold, the stupidity:<br /><img src="http://www.mediafire.com/convkey/56cc/r4fd1okeo1t7yc7zg.jpg?size_id=8" alt="" /><br />AND NOW...let there be download link! (and then there was a download link: <a href="http://www.mediafire.com/download/725kkoapirjagsd/BloatedAero.zip" class="postlink">http://www.mediafire.com/download/725kkoapirjagsd/BloatedAero.zip</a>)<br /><br />EDIT: BorderSkin is not associated with Classic Shell in any way at all, whatsoever, and no-one on this board is responsible for any problems you may have with it. In fact, I have a feeling I probably shouldn't even have mentioned it at all...meh, too late now .-.<br /><br />EDIT 2: Woops, wrong download link <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_lol.gif" alt=":lol:" title="Laughing" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9454">Splitwirez</a> — Sun Oct 11, 2015 4:04 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
